  "texts": [
    "As can be seen in Fig. 25, the studies use various normalization methods such as standardized normal distribution (N = 11, 5%), Z-score (N = 6, 3%), Min-Max (N = 4, 2%), and Rectified Linear Unit (N = 3, 1%).",
    "Some other techniques reported are Global normalization, Local normalization, and L1/2 normalization in a small number of studies with a total of 5% (N = 12).",
    "In addition, 84% of them did not mentioned any technique explicitly.",
    "Feature extraction and selection Feature extractionFeatures are commonly extracted from frequency, time, frequency-time, and wavelet domains in EEG-based emotion recognition studies.",
    "Figure 26 indicates the feature extraction domains implemented in the reviewed studies."
